Hundreds of gun owners are exchanging their firearms for gift cards to buy groceries in Los Angeles in a buyback program aiming to get weapons off the streets.

Lines of cars and people stretched around the block in the first hours of the exchange on Wednesday morning to take advantage of a guns-for-groceries exchange program that was moved up in the wake of the Connecticut school shooting.

Police officers filled bins with a variety of rifles and handguns outside the Los Angeles Memorial Sports Arena and the Van Nuys Masonic Temple.

